      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl3",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalised index of haemolysis (NIH), which is the regulatory-accepted metric for blood pump hemolysis per FDA guidance (2021). Secondary QoIs (velocity magnitude, wall shear stress) are mechanistically linked to hemolysis model inputs. QoI traceability matrix maps each model output to a COU decision variable."
