      "rationale": "All model inputs (viscosity, density, hemolysis coefficients, inlet velocity profile, rotational speed) characterised with probability distributions from literature and experimental measurements. Monte Carlo sampling (n = 2 000, Latin hypercube) propagates input uncertainty to NIH predictions. Input sensitivity analysis identifies hemolysis exponent α as dominant contributor (Sobol index 0.61)."
    },
